newsitem.title: USA: Calif. distillates unscathed by East Coast squeeze.
newsitem.headline: Calif. distillates unscathed by East Coast squeeze.

text.p: As most U.S. markets brace for higher prices and lower supplies of distillates this winter, the warm-weather California market is expected to ride out the season unscathed.

With supplies in the region flush and demand for heating oil minimal, the recent rise in West Coast distillates prices has been the result mainly of a rash of refinery problems and is not a reflection of the broader rise in other regions, analysts said.
